snippet.textDisplay:
Recovering Opiate addict here and I wanna say this hit me hard. When your lost in the drugs to make you numb you shut yourself out and start to think no one cares or wants to listen. You just want anyone to tell you, you don't need these your are strong and I have your back.


Luckily, I have my daughter, mom and brother who would cut, smash and break through that dark room I was in and gave me the hope I need to get better and help myself. Now I'm 5 years sober and have a job, eating healthy and seeing a psychiatrist and am on medication for Bipolar and severe anxiety. Like is so hard sometimes, but now I now there is a light through that darkness you have to fight when your tired and feel like you can't move, but just pushing yourself through you will get out and the air that hits you when you get out and feels refreshing you can be at ease and be with those you love and have fun.


I fight everyday reminded of those who lost the battle and killed themselves or overdosed. I fight for them cause I have to live life I belong here in this world and will always pray and remember them to give me strength to move forward.


Thank you, Demi. Your songs are powerful and hold so much emotion it's beautiful.
